---
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="Trust & Scientific Editorial Policies | EquiToolkit" description="Our clinical and mathematical calculators are derived from research by veterinary councils (AAEP, NRC, UC Davis). Learn about our standards.">
  <div class="page-wrap">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-right"></i>
      <span>Trust Center</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="page-hero">
      <div class="hero-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-user-shield"></i></div>
      <h1>EquiToolkit Editorial & Trust Policies</h1>
      <p>Veterinary credibility is the foundation of our work. Learn about our meticulous review process, disclaimer rules, and strict contributor standards.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="content-box">
      <section>
        <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-microscope"></i> 1. Clinical Review Process</h2>
        <p>All physiological models, feed analyses, medication formulas, and deworming strategies are cross-referenced with peer-reviewed studies published by major veterinary councils:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>American Association of Equine Practitioners (AAEP) guidelines</li>
          <li>United States National Research Council (NRC) Nutrient Requirements of Horses</li>
          <li>UC Davis School of Veterinary Medicine Equine Research Center databases</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation"></i> 2. Medical Disclaimer</h2>
        <div class="alert-box">
          <strong>NOTICE:</strong> The calculations, estimators, and library articles are for educational and exploratory purposes only. They are NOT designed to substitute, override, or delay direct professional veterinary consultations. In acute emergencies, always contact your veterinarian immediately.
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-pen-nib"></i> 3. Authorship & Contributor Standards</h2>
        <p>Articles and health files are authored by qualified equine professionals, veterinary students, or experienced stable operations managers. Each module is peer-reviewed by an advisory veterinary board. No promotional, paid, or affiliate bias influences our directory.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .page-wrap { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem; }
  .breadcrumbs { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .breadcrumbs a { color: var(--text-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .breadcrumbs a:hover { color: var(--primary); }
  .breadcrumbs i { font-size: 0.7rem; }

  .page-hero { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .hero-icon { font-size: 3rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page-hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); }
  .page-hero p { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .content-box { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 2rem; }
  .content-box section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .content-box h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 0.8rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .content-box h2 i { color: var(--primary); }
  .content-box p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
  .content-box ul { list-style: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .content-box li { padding: 0.3rem 0; }
  .alert-box { background: #fff5f5; border: 2px solid #e74c3c; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 1rem; color: #a71d2a; font-size: 0.85rem; }
</style>